            <main>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">How to Find Trending Brands & Emerging Merchants</h1>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>The Problem</th><th>The AI Solution</th></tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Finding new, high-traffic, or "up-and-coming" brands to target is a manual, time-consuming research task.</td>
                        <td>Use Gemini Advanced as a powerful, instant research assistant to identify emerging brands and explain *why* they are trending.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <div class="tag-container">
                    <span class="tag tag-green"><strong>Primary Roles:</strong> Account Directors, Account Managers</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-green"><strong>Tools:</strong> Gemini Advanced (standalone)</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-green"><strong>Difficulty / Phase:</strong> Super Easy Win</span>
                </div>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4 solution-h2">Step-by-Step Training Workflow</h2>
                <p class="mb-4">This workflow will show you how to use Gemini as a creative partner to find new opportunities you might have missed.</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 1: Open Gemini Advanced</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Go directly to the standalone Gemini web interface (<code>gemini.google.com</code>) to get the most powerful, up-to-date answers.</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 2: Ask a "Market Research" Prompt</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">The key is to ask Gemini to act as an expert and to find *emerging* brands, not just the obvious market leaders.</p>
                <p><strong>For finding new merchants:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>Act as a market analyst for e-commerce.
What are 5 "emerging" brands in the [Home Goods] category?
For each, provide a 1-sentence summary and a key reason why they are gaining traffic (e.g., "social media buzz," "unique product").</code></pre>
                <p class="mt-4"><strong>For finding competitor audiences:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>I am building a target audience list for [Merchant Name, e.g., "Allbirds"].
What are its 5 main competitors, AND 5 "indirect" competitors?
Format this as a simple list.</code></pre>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 3: Refine and Go Deeper</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">The first answer is just the start. Use the follow-up questions to build your strategy.</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 pl-4">
                    <li>"For brands 1 and 3, what is their primary marketing strategy?"</li>
                    <li>"Which of these brands have an active affiliate program?"</li>
                    <li>"Write a short, 2-paragraph outreach email to [Emerging Brand Name], explaining what our company does and why they would be a good partner."</li>
                </ul>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Pro-Tip: Use NotebookLM to Track Your Research</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">When you find interesting new brands, create a "New Merchant Research" project in <strong>NotebookLM</strong>. Copy and paste your Gemini conversations into a Google Doc and upload it as a "source." Your NotebookLM becomes a "brain" of all your research.</p>
                <pre><code>Based on all my research sources, which 3 trending brands seem to have the biggest affiliate marketing push right now?</code></pre>
